<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2018/02/07/spring-cloud-for-google-cloud-platform-1-0-milestone-2-available">Spring Cloud for Google Cloud Platform 1.0 Milestone 2 Available</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon releases"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/releases">Releases</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/2158ce6e7c048277890eb64458864c1c?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<a class="author" href="/team/artembilan">Artem Bilan</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2018-02-07 19:24:11.277">February 7, 2018</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="3162" href="/blog/2018/02/07/spring-cloud-for-google-cloud-platform-1-0-milestone-2-available#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Dear Spring Community!</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>It’s my pleasure to announce today a new project in the <a href="https://projects.spring.io/spring-cloud/">Spring Cloud</a> family. It’s called <code>Spring Cloud GCP</code> and its goal is to bring into your applications well-known Spring patterns and Spring Boot conventions for consuming <a href="https://cloud.google.com">Google Cloud Platform</a> services.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The project currently is in version <code>1.0.0.M2</code> and is available from the <a href="https://repo.spring.io/milestone/org/springframework/cloud">Spring Milestone Repository</a>:</p>
</div>
<div class="listingblock">
<div class="content">
<pre class="prettyprint highlight"><code class="language-xml" data-lang="xml">&lt;dependencyManagement&gt;
   &lt;dependencies&gt;
       &lt;dependency&gt;
           &lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.cloud&lt;/groupId&gt;
           &lt;artifactId&gt;spring-cloud-gcp-dependencies&lt;/artifactId&gt;
           &lt;version&gt;1.0.0.M2&lt;/version&gt;
           &lt;type&gt;pom&lt;/type&gt;
           &lt;scope&gt;import&lt;/scope&gt;
       &lt;/dependency&gt;
   &lt;/dependencies&gt;
&lt;/dependencyManagement&gt;</code></pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<a class="blog-preview--readmore desktop-only" href="/blog/2018/02/07/spring-cloud-for-google-cloud-platform-1-0-milestone-2-available">
Read more...
</a>
</article>
